<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-23-0999 </DOCNO><TEXT>The most important factors that influence the economical value of a windpower plant connected to the grid are discussed. A cost-benefit analysisof wind turbines and placing wind turbines in a wind power plant is given.By considering costs and benefits integral the setting up of a wind powerplant can be optimized. Limiting conditions have to be taken into account.Both a cost-benefit analysis and optimization of the wind power plantcan determine the energy price. 9 figs., 1 ref.</TEXT></DOC>